      <description>&lt;p&gt;Hm many people know Mastodon but not its enabling layer: ActivityPub/Webfinger.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The irony is that (de)federation/banning-features can re-enshittify open protocols (serving dictator-admins-first, users later).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Perhaps it indicates a personal confusion: maybe what interests me about the Fediverse is Webfinger, then ActivityPub, then platforms (Mastodon/Peertube/Lemmy e.g.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
